This paper is primarily focused on improving the training and generalization performance of neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of Dropout, a regularization technique commonly used in machine learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments involving computer vision tasks, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the biologically inspired architecture of Parallel Circuits, which could potentially fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
